menu.item_name: La Legende Sancerre (Sauvignon Blanc) (Loire Valley, France) Glass
menu.description: Bright and unusually juicy for a Sancerre, with marvelous zing to the white peach, lemon and flint notes, which glisten as they carry through on the palate. Light melon and mineral notes add volume and grace to the racy finish. A superb Sancerre, at a great price! Ideal with seafood, poultry, and veggie dishes.

menu.item_name: Lhuillier Brut Tradition NV, Champagne, France
menu.description: A delightful Champagne from a family owned growers co-op, this is perfect for special occasions, birthdays, and celebrations. A fresh nose with hints of white fruits, it opens with delightful soft apple and toasty notes. Perfect with seafood dishes, plays well with naan and samosas.

An intense mousse and a bright cherry colour, pronounced aromas of ripe strawberry and cherry and an elegant acidity adding freshness while pairing harmoniously with the discrete presence of sugars create a wine that is at the same time dynamic and balanced.

menu.item_name: Elisabetta Abrami, Franciacorta Brut Ros (NV) Italy
menu.description: The bouquet is intriguing and firm, with balanced red fruits such as cherry and blackberry, perfectly balanced and a nice freshness. One of the best ross you will find in Franciacorta. The bubbles are fine and linger in the mouth for a long time.

menu.item_name: Jean Vesselle, Champagne Brut Ros (NV) France
menu.description: A delightful Champagne from a family owned growers co-op, this is perfect for special occasions, birthdays, and celebrations. A fresh nose with hints of white fruits, it opens with delightful soft apple and toasty notes. Perfect with seafood dishes, plays well with naan and samosas.

menu.item_name: La Scolca Gavi Di Gavi 2020, Piemonte, Italy
menu.description: A delightful Gavi made of 100% Cortese from the oldest winemaker in the appellation. Straw colored with a great body and well balanced bracing acidity. Great with seafood and vegetable dishes.

Very pure nose, with delicate fruitiness, complemented by floral notes and a beautiful iodized minerality, mixed with controlled aging touches. This finely buttered cuve, imbued with the freshness of Chardonnay, also reveals beautiful aromas of lime blossom, liquorice, menthol and fresh hazelnut. In tension, finesse and energy, the touch evokes a caressing velvet.

menu.item_name: Domaine Besson, Givry Le Haut Colombier Blanc (2019)
menu.description: A pale lemon in colour with white peaches and floral nuances on the nose. The palate is round with notes of white blossom, candied lemon peel, peaches and a soft, creamy character. The rounded mouthfeel is nicely balanced by an elegant acidity and a long finish.

Aromas of lemons, white fruits, light herbs, lemon zest, wild fern and linden blossom. At their best, the wines are rich and full-bodied, with a tangy, flinty note in each sip. Nose : The wine has a very open and fiery nose infused with burnt wood mixed with vanilla extracts and roasted chestnuts. Palate : Mineral and delicate; concentrated characteristics of mainly fresh fruit like peach and pear.

This delightful Chardonnay is a treat! A distinct Chablis style of vine peaches, banana, citrus and a touch of brioche. The palate is well-balanced between richness, freshness and elegance. Great with seafood, lighter chicken and vegetable dishes, as well as naan.

menu.item_name: Small Vines Wines, Sonoma Coast Chardonnay, CA (2017)
menu.description: Has a nose of pretty blossoms & floral notes, butterscotch rounds out with citrus peel, tangerine and green apple. A nice weight and creamy texture with a long white tea finish. 93 Points Vinous

menu.item_name: Stealth Cabernet Sauvignon 2018, Napa Valley, California
menu.description: A lighter style Cabernet made from younger vines (sourced from Caymus and Nickel and Nickel plts), this is a great combatant for hearty dishes with spice. Lovely vanilla notes with fresh blackberry.
Bright, ripe red fruit with some nutty elements on the nose and palate. Medium to full body with crisp, spicy fruit flavor, unobtrusive tannins and a clean, spicy finish.

menu.item_name: Highway 12 Highwaymen Reserve Cabernet Sauvignon, Sonoma County, California
menu.description: Made by Michael Sebastiani, this Sonoma treat is made from the best blocks of Highway 12s grapes. American oak and spicebox hits of flavor abound, and the wine works great with medium to heavy dishes.
A great Amarone at an awesome value. Great red fruit notes, hints of spice and a great finish. Food pairings are many- this wine works with just about any dish, save for seafood.

menu.item_name: Andrew Rich Eola-Amity Hills 2018, Willamette Valley, Oregon
menu.description: 2017 Sweet and seamless in texture, showing very good depth and energy to the raspberry, boysenberry and dark chocolate flavors, harmonious notes of dark cherry and coffee lead to a pleasing finish. A great catch all wine that pairs well with all- or on its own! 92 Points-WE

menu.item_name: Poseidon Vineyard Estate Pinot Noir 2019, Carneros, Napa Valley, California
menu.description: A rarity! A Pinot Noir that rests in Hungarian Oak shows fresh strawberry, Bing cherries, leather and an earthy undertone. Flavors are beautifully woven togetherred fruit, dried raspberries in particular, root-beer and a lift of baking spice. Tannins are integrated and silky. A wine of great balance and harmonious flow. Great with chicken and spicy dishes!

menu.item_name: Obsidian Ridge Estate Red Hills Cabernet Sauvignon 2019, Lake County, California
menu.description: Flavors of dark chocolate, coffee and fresh blackberry are carried on silky tanninsthey speak clearly, but dont shout. Great by itself or with lamb and heartier chicken dishes. 93 Points- WineMag

menu.item_name: Knudsen Vineyards, Pinot Noir Dundee Hills (2018)
menu.description: Winemaker Nate Klostermann has nailed this one perfectly. The pinpoint fruit flavors conjoin raspberry, spicy cranberry and Bing cherry. The aging in 20% new French oak adds a touch of toast and could benefit from further bottle age. What is Especially lovely is the way the wine coats the palate, the highlights of baking spices and the soft, silky tannins. Drink with pleasure immediately or age a bit longer to bring out all of the depth and detail. Wine Enthusiast 93 Points

menu.item_name: Avid, Cabernet Sauvignon (Spring Mountain District) CA.(2017)
menu.description: The 2017 vintage is showing classic characteristics of Spring Mountain. On the nose the wine shows cedar, cassis, tobacco and vanilla and on the palate presents notes of blackberry, plum and cocoa integrated with a layer of bright red fruits. Smooth oak and tannins balance out the fruit.

menu.item_name: Reynolds Family Winery (CA), Napa Valley Cabernet Sauvignon Estate (2018)
menu.description: Great characteristics of blackberry, dark cherry, chocolate, tobacco, and just a hint of spice. A long velvety finish with soft but structured tannins makes it enjoyable now and through the next decade.

menu.item_name: Small Vines Wines, Small Vines Pinot Noir Sonoma Coast (2018)
menu.description: Great color from flesh of fig to deep ruby. Nose begins with black cherry and blue fruits. Energetic acidity and tart red-fruits are balanced by succulent richness finishing with pleasing tobacco, dry chocolate, and sage. 94 Points Wine Enthusiast

Groth Cabernet Sauvignon is an alluring shade of deep purple-red, concentrated to the edge of the glass. A spectrum of aromas bound from the glass: blackberry, red currant, coffee, dusty cocoa, and white pepper. On the palate, flavors are beautifully held in balance by the fine, chalky tannin, its initial grip slowly melting to a long, silky finish. Interwoven notes of sour cherry, red raspberry, and chocolate invite another sip. Tandoori and curry items are perfectly match with this delicious wine.

menu.item_name: Double Eagle Red 2018, Napa Valley, California
menu.description: A classic Bordeaux blend culled from premier vineyards in Oakville and St Helena. It opens with intense aromatics of bramble berry and currant, nuanced by notes of vanilla and oak spice from 20 months in French oak barrels. Made by the multiple time winner of Winemaker of the Year Philippe Melka (Wine Enthusiast, Wine Advocate). Lamb is the move here to match it. 94 Points-Tasting Panel, 91 Points- WA

menu.item_name: Meyer Family Le Bon Bon Cabernet Sauvignon, (Napa Valley)
menu.description: Aromas spring to life with ripe plum and blackberries jumping out of the glass, without American Oak. Two years in oak have softened the palate, making this a very approachable Oakville red wine. About as limited as Silver Oak Wines and equally delicious, this rarity is an irresistible offer at a fantastic price.
